modules.description: Provides literal syntax for arbitrary-precision integers and rationals, enabling direct use of Z and Q types in code. Handles parsing and validation of numeric literals at compile time, ensuring correct representation. Used to write precise mathematical expressions without runtime conversion overhead.

Provides syntax extensions for parsing and pretty-printing arbitrary-precision integers and rational numbers. Recognizes the `z` and `q` prefixes to distinguish between Zarith types and standard integers. Supports seamless integration with OCaml's pretty-printing system for enhanced readability. Allows developers to work with large numbers in a natural, readable format within code.
